14.Name: Cave Entrance

15.Description: A damp, musty opening with walls of rock and faintly glowing crystals. Make sure to not get lost in these dark, twisting catacombs...
15.Name: Cave Start

16.Description: A small enclosed area with the pale ashes of a fire once burned. Many a soul came through here, telling stories and sharing drinks. None remain. Lost to time.
16.Name: Old Fire

17.Description: A thick lair of smoggy, acrid gas hangs in the air here. Old, tattered tents lay bloodied and rotting. This area may be more dangerous than originally thought.
17.Name: Abandoned Camp

18.Description: An open area unveils itself in front of you, with rock outcroppings and flat ground. The blood from the previous room seems to lead into here. Something deep down feels wrong in here, be wary.
18.Name: Ambush

19.Description: This seems to be where those monsters were camping out. Be careful, there may still be some lurking about... As you look further into the camp you can see the decaying, charred, and maimed humanoid figures tied to wooden poles.
19.Name: Enemy Camp

20.Description: Those creatures seem to have been trying to keep something out. There is a wooden blockade and spikes lining it that seem to have been destroyed recently. Green liquid seems to have once coated the ground here before drying into a sticky mess.
20.Name: Blockade

21.Description: The path here seems to have been coated in both new and old webs. Some seem to be burned to the south.
21.Name: Webbed Corridor

22.Description: There is still a smoldering fire here, and a relatively clean sleeping bag, you know, for cave standards. This feels like a safe place to rest and recover energy. You have a feeling that the path ahead will be much more treacherous.
22.Name: Cave Rest

23.Description: After the calm fire of the area before, this is not quite what you were expecting... There are webs everywhere, bloodied bodies of monsters and humans alike. The rocks here seem to have been melted by some sort of acid, while the air has an unnaturally cold aura. Prepare for a fight, because nothing about this room says it will be easy.
23.Name: Spider Den

24.Description: The big one is coming. The webs here are extra thick and sticky; you can tell that one misstep means demise. This will be your hardest foe since you entered this cave system, so I hope you know what you are doing. The bodies and stench seem to have multiplied here. Whatever is here must have quite the appetite. Will you be its next meal?
24.Name: Spider Boss

25.Description: After that fight with the spider you continue on to deeper within the cave. The rocky walls seem more and more polished as you go on, becoming smoother and smoother, until they seem almost man-made. A strange smell that seems to be a mix of fresh blood and incense floods your senses. The rocky, uneven ground seems to even out before shifting into the soft velvet of a royal red runway carpet. The dampness of the earlier areas has subsided to a comfortable level, and the off-putting cold from the spider's layer has warmed to the perfect lounging temperature. Too bad you're not lounging, and your gear starts to become uncomfortably warm. The walls shift from rocks to rich, dark wood planks that you have only seen in noble places. Everything seems too nice to be in a grungy cave... It sends a chill down your spine.
25.Name: Cave Hall

26.Description: As you reach the end of the runway, your gaze meets the imposing figure of a set of double doors. Each at least 10 feet in size and made of a dark, sturdy wood. Gold accents line the door, while two large gargoyles sit posed upon pillars of gold. On the doors there is a plaque made of solid gold that reads, 'Here lies the protectors of the Dark Father Estate, Goliath and Victor.' Something about those stone statues makes you scared to turn your back to them on an instinctual level...
26.Name: Main Hall

27.Description: After you passed those gargoyles, the doors open by themselves. As you walk in, you are greeted with the largest room you have ever been in. The floors are made of plush red velvet and rich midnight grain walnut, as the carpet leads to a set of two grand staircases. Between these two staircases, there lay two pictures framed on the wall. One of a porcelain pale bust, with long, angular features, high cheekbones and a narrow jawline. The eyes are dark and red, feeling as if staring directly into your soul. Their hair is long and dark, almost unnaturally so, falling past their shoulders onto their noble regalia. They are wearing a black cape around their shoulders lined with red and gold, as a shirt has a high collar and is perfectly white, as if it was just made. Their shoulders are wide and defined as they lead up their neck, of which is uncomfortably thick and thin at the same time. The other picture framed on the wall below the first is of a similar figure, with the same white skin, clean attire, and long dark hair, but their face seems to have been torn out while there are dried blood splatters across the canvas. This room seems to be well traveled, as you have the bad feeling of being watched...
27.Name: Foyer

48.Description: After all those battles you feel weak and as if you could collapse at any moment. Just when you are ready to give in you find a quaint bedroom up the stairs, as you open the door you find a room that looks as if it would belong to a young girl, with bedding and accesories of baby pink ~3~3~s . Your too tired to care about your pride and rest in a pink bed, you feel safe here.
48.Name: Castle Rest

49.Description: As you leave that nice room, you are greeted with a long hall, identical to all the others, but this one just feels off. There are too many doors on each side, almost as if they are all entreances for something bad... you get the feeling you will have to prepare yourself for a fight
49.Name: Uncomfortable Hall

50.Description: As you continue on deeper into the castle, you walk apon a grand sized ball room. DDCCDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDstumble apon a grand sized ball room. The floor is made of black marble and there are crystal tables set on the perimeter of the room. On those tables there are crystal wine glasses, some still half full of what you at least hope is wine, but have a feeling is not. you see movement in the corner of your eye and feel a bloodthirsty chill run down your spine.
50.Name: Ball Room

51.Description: As you continue walking through the rooms of this vast castle, you find yourself stumbling apon a large set of doors, similar to the entrance, although they are smaller and have dark iron engravings. They brandish large door knockers of iron and gold, with bats holding human skulls in their claws. The hall holds a gargoyle perched atop a rest above the door as two pillars seem to conceal something behind them on the left and right. Something tells you that you arent a welcome guest here.
51.Name: Final Hall

52.Description: As you open the doors to the final room you are greeted by a large throne. Perched atop that throne is a figure that demands authority. The throne holds the count himself. His regal glory the same as his portrait. White shining skin, and this freatures. You feel fear shoot through your body as he sips from a glass of red liquid before throwing it across the room at you. The red liquid splashed on you as the glass shatters at your feet, he stands up and lets his cape flow behind him. His clothes seem to morph into something sturdier and stiffer. As you prepare yourself for the fight of your life, your legs shake and your arms feel weak, you can hear the blood rushing into your ears. You steady yourself and prepare for the  of your life
52.Name: Final Boss

53.Description: You have reached the end of the demo, thank you for playing!
53.Name: End
